3. what is main.jsx why we use?

main.jsx is the entry file of a React application.
It is the file where the React app starts running.

We use it to:

1.Import React
2.Import the main App component
3.Connect React to the HTML file
4.Render the app into the browser

4. what is babel compiler?

Babel is a JavaScript compiler.
It converts modern JavaScript and JSX code into older JavaScript that browsers can understand.

jsx -> Babel -> js -> run browser

5. what is virtual dom? and real dom?

Real DOM (Document Object Model) is the actual structure of the webpage created by the browser.
Exists inside browser memory
Directly updates the screen
Is slower when many changes happen

Virtual DOM is a lightweight copy of the Real DOM stored in memory.
React to update the Real DOM efficiently.
Is not visible to the user
Compares old and new versions (diffing)
Updates only changed parts in Real DOM
Makes apps faster
